<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Body strongly depressed dorsoventrally and minutely granulate (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Fig. 3. Live Amorphopus notabilis from Brazilian Amazon." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395608" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">3</figureCitation>
). Eyes globose, not prominent; vertex anteriorly truncated; face very distinctly oblique; frontal costa with a wide scutellum between the lower part of the eyes, slightly compressed-elevated, sinuate below (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2B</figureCitation>
). Lateral lobes of pronotum outwardly ampliate with both margins undulate. Tegmina oval and wings to the pronotum apex (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2C</figureCitation>
). Legs short, fore and middle femora flattened, foliaceous and clypeate (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1E, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2E, F</figureCitation>
), antegenicular tooth of the hind femur slightly developed, hind tibia very sparingly spinose, minutely serrulate; the first and third articles of the hind tarsi equal in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
